Anyone who says Manning choked in #SB48 didn't pay attention to the game. All they see is the score.
They don't realize that Seattle's DEFENSE shut down Manning. Even though he threw a SB-record-setting number of completions to Demaryius Thomas (13). And threw SB-record-setting number of completions, total (34).
You wanna accuse someone of choking in Super Bowl XLVIII? Blame the Denver defense, who allowed Seattle's offense to score 18 unanswered points (3 TDs). Meanwhile, the Seattle D only scored 8 points (2 from safety. 6 on INT TD.) And the special teams scored 17 points (1 TD, 2FGs, 5PATs.)
Did Manning throw a few interceptions? Sure. But there's a bit of something everyone forgets, when playing against Seattle's "Legion of Boom"; just about every QB throws an interception to them.

I have respect for Manning and Denver. He's a class act who hasn't had to cheat to be successful, and that makes him truly a G.O.A.T.

For the 3rd time this season and the 13th time in her career, Maya Moore is the Western Conference Player of the Week! Maya led the league with 23.3 points per game, was sixth in assists (3.8) and seventh in rebounding (7.3). She was named MVP of the Boost Mobile AllStar game on July 25 after posting a record 30 points, 6 rebounds and 5 assists in a victory. 

Moore has scored 20+ points in 11-straight games, tying Cynthia Cooper for the second-longest such streak in WNBA history.

One more 20-point game, and she ties Taurasi's record and the league record.  Two more 20-point games, she breaks yet another WNBA record!
